{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01Rdi4AQRYyQNDYkBHTdCsLd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup. The access logs are using the default format (not the required one with OTel trace/span IDs), and OTel isn't enabled. I need to:\n\n1. Edit the `ingress-nginx-controller` ConfigMap to add:\n   - `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"` \n   - `opentelemetry-config` pointing to the OTel collector\n   - `opentelemetry-trust-incoming-span: \"true\"` \n   - `otlp-collector-host: otel-collector.otel.svc`\n   - `otlp-collector-port: \"4317\"`\n   - `opentelemetry-sample-rate: \"1.0\"` for full sampling\n   - `log-format-upstream` configured to include trace and span IDs\n\nI should verify the ingress-nginx controller version supports these OTel configuration keys, since v1.14.1 should have built-in OpenTelemetry support. default sampling rate is 0.01, and I need to make sure the access log format includes the OpenTelemetry trace and span ID variables. The log format string spans multiple lines with proper escaping for the ConfigMap, though I need to verify how NGINX handles the newlines in the format specification. The `log-format-upstream` value from the ConfigMap gets inserted directly into the nginx.conf template, so if there are literal newlines in the format string, they'll create a multi-line log format in NGINX itself. I see the format string spans multiple lines with the newlines preserved as specified. Now I need to patch the ConfigMap with the OTel configuration settings, including enabling OpenTelemetry, setting the collector host and port for the ingress-nginx controller.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1858,"cache_read_input_tokens":30584,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1858},"output_tokens":21,"service_tier":"standard","infer